The article is a transcript of remarks made by Vice President Mike Pence at the Pentagon during the full honors ceremony for Secretary of Defense Mark T. Esper. Pence praises President Trump for his efforts to strengthen the military, including securing the largest increase in national defense funding in a generation and the largest military pay raise in over 10 years. Pence also mentions the President's direction in producing a National Security Strategy, pursuing the modernization of the nuclear arsenal, and the establishment of the United States Space Force. He highlights the upcoming budget deal that will preserve investments in national defense and end the defense sequester. Pence expresses confidence in Secretary Esper's ability to lead the Department of Defense. The article ends with Pence introducing President Trump.